"Description for enum type: ProtocolType"
enum ProtocolType {
  "Represents a protocol for exchanging assets"
  EXCHANGE
  "Represents a protocol for lending assets"
  LENDING
  "Represents a protocol for generating yield"
  YIELD
  "Represents a protocol for bridging assets across networks"
  BRIDGE
  "Represents a generic protocol type"
  GENERIC
}

"Description for table: Token"
type Token @entity @regularPolling {
  "Unique identifier for the token, stored as bytes."
  id: Bytes!
  "Name of the token."
  name: String!
  "Symbol representing the token."
  symbol: String!
  "Number of decimal places used by the token."
  decimals: Int!
  "The last recorded price of the token in USD."
  lastPriceUSD: BigDecimal
  "Block number at which the last price was recorded."
  lastPriceBlockNumber: BigInt
  "Type of the token, defined by the TokenType enum."
  type: TokenType
  "Associated market for the token."
  _market: Market
  "Internal attribute for token type classification."
  _iavsTokenType: String
}

"Description for enum type: RewardTokenType"
enum RewardTokenType {
  "Represents a reward token type for deposits"
  DEPOSIT
  "Represents a reward token type for variable borrowings"
  VARIABLE_BORROW
  "Represents a reward token type for stable borrowings"
  STABLE_BORROW
  "Represents a reward token type for staking"
  STAKE
}

"Description for table: RewardToken"
type RewardToken @entity @regularPolling {
  "Unique identifier for the reward token"
  id: ID!
  "Reference to the associated token entity"
  token: Token!
  "Specifies the type of reward token"
  type: RewardTokenType!
  "Timestamp indicating when the distribution ends"
  _distributionEnd: BigInt
}

"Description for enum type: LendingType"
enum LendingType {
  "Description for column: CDP"
  CDP
  "Description for column: POOLED"
  POOLED
}

"Description for enum type: PermissionType"
enum PermissionType {
  "Access is restricted to a predefined list of users."
  WHITELIST_ONLY
  "Access is granted based on specific permissions."
  PERMISSIONED
  "Access is open to all users without restrictions."
  PERMISSIONLESS
  "Access is reserved for administrative users with full control."
  ADMIN
}

"Description for enum type: RiskType"
enum RiskType {
  "Represents a global risk type"
  GLOBAL
  "Represents an isolated risk type"
  ISOLATED
}

"Description for enum type: CollateralizationType"
enum CollateralizationType {
  "Indicates that the collateral exceeds the required amount"
  OVER_COLLATERALIZED
  "Indicates that the collateral is less than the required amount"
  UNDER_COLLATERALIZED
  "Indicates that there is no collateral"
  UNCOLLATERALIZED
}

"Description for enum type: TokenType"
enum TokenType {
  "Indicates a token that adjusts its supply periodically."
  REBASING
  "Indicates a token with a fixed supply that does not adjust."
  NON_REBASING
}

"Description for enum type: InterestRateType"
enum InterestRateType {
  "Represents an interest rate that remains constant over time."
  STABLE
  "Represents an interest rate that can change over time based on market conditions."
  VARIABLE
  "Represents an interest rate that is set at a specific level for the duration of the term."
  FIXED
}

"Description for enum type: InterestRateSide"
enum InterestRateSide {
  "Represents the perspective of the lender in an interest rate agreement."
  LENDER
  "Represents the perspective of the borrower in an interest rate agreement."
  BORROWER
}

"Description for enum type: Tranche"
enum Tranche {
  "Represents the senior tranche, typically having priority in repayment."
  SENIOR
  "Represents the junior tranche, usually subordinate in repayment priority."
  JUNIOR
}

"Description for enum type: PositionSide"
enum PositionSide {
  "Represents the side of a financial transaction that provides security or guarantee."
  COLLATERAL
  "Represents the side of a financial transaction that receives funds or assets."
  BORROWER
}

"Description for table: InterestRate"
type InterestRate @entity @regularPolling {
  "Unique identifier for the interest rate entry"
  id: ID!
  "The interest rate value as a decimal"
  rate: BigDecimal!
  "The duration for which the interest rate is applicable, in some unit of time"
  duration: Int
  "The block number at which the interest rate matures"
  maturityBlock: BigInt
  "The side of the interest rate, indicating whether it is a borrowing or lending rate"
  side: InterestRateSide!
  "The type of interest rate, such as fixed or variable"
  type: InterestRateType!
  "The tranche associated with the interest rate, if applicable"
  tranche: Tranche
}

"Description for enum type: FeeType"
enum FeeType {
  "Fee charged during the liquidation process"
  LIQUIDATION_FEE
  "Fee charged for administrative purposes"
  ADMIN_FEE
  "Fee associated with the protocol"
  PROTOCOL_FEE
  "Fee for minting operations"
  MINT_FEE
  "Fee for withdrawal transactions"
  WITHDRAW_FEE
  "Protocol fee for flashloan services"
  FLASHLOAN_PROTOCOL_FEE
  "Liquidity provider fee for flashloan services"
  FLASHLOAN_LP_FEE
  "Other types of fees not specified"
  OTHER
}

"Description for table: Fee"
type Fee @entity @regularPolling {
  "A unique identifier for each fee entry."
  id: ID!
  "Represents the percentage rate of the fee."
  rate: BigDecimal
  "Represents a fixed amount charged as a fee."
  flatFee: BigDecimal
  "Specifies the category or classification of the fee."
  type: FeeType!
}

"Description for table: RevenueDetail"
type RevenueDetail @entity @regularPolling {
  "Unique identifier for the revenue detail entry."
  id: Bytes!
  "List of fees representing different revenue sources."
  sources: [Fee!]!
  "List of monetary amounts in USD corresponding to each revenue source."
  amountsUSD: [BigDecimal!]!
}

"Description for enum type: OracleSource"
enum OracleSource {
  "Represents the Uniswap decentralized exchange."
  UNISWAP
  "Represents the Balancer decentralized exchange."
  BALANCER
  "Represents the Chainlink decentralized oracle network."
  CHAINLINK
  "Represents the Yearn Finance yield aggregator."
  YEARN
  "Represents the Sushiswap decentralized exchange."
  SUSHISWAP
  "Represents the Curve Finance decentralized exchange."
  CURVE
}

"Description for table: Oracle"
type Oracle @entity @regularPolling {
  "Unique identifier for the Oracle entity"

  blockCreated: BigInt!

  timestampCreated: BigInt!

  isActive: Boolean!
  "Indicates if the oracle is related to USD"
  isUSD: Boolean!
  "Hash value when the oracle ended"
  hashEnded: Bytes
  "Source of the oracle data"

}

"Description for column: Oracle"
interface Protocol {
  """Unique identifier for the protocol"""
  id: Bytes!
  """Name of the protocol"""

  """Version of the schema used by the protocol"""

  """Version of the subgraph used by the protocol"""

  """Version of the methodology used by the protocol"""

  """Network on which the protocol operates"""

  """Type of the protocol"""

  """Type of lending mechanism used by the protocol"""
  lendingType: LendingType
  """Permission type required for lenders"""

  """Permission type required for borrowers"""

  """Permission type required for pool creators"""

  """Type of risk associated with the protocol"""

  """Type of collateralization used by the protocol"""

  """Total value locked in USD within the protocol"""
  totalValueLockedUSD: BigDecimal!
  """Value controlled by the protocol in USD"""
  protocolControlledValueUSD: BigDecimal
  """Cumulative number of unique users"""
  cumulativeUniqueUsers: Int!
  """Cumulative number of unique transaction signers"""
  cumulativeUniqueTxSigners: Int!
  """Cumulative revenue from the supply side in USD"""

  """Cumulative revenue from the protocol side in USD"""

  """Cumulative total revenue in USD"""
